    "body": "### Problem\n\nVarious symbols (supported by font and terminal) can be rendered everywhere in neovim, except virtual text. Here they are replaced by ■, despite the prefix being to set to something else (like ●). This wasn't a problem in 0.11.7; but is a problem in new 0.12.1 release.\n\n<img width=\"543\" height=\"61\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/426745a8-d3fc-4b0f-9fa7-0f8b57a9c0bc\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n/\n\n### Expected behavior\n\n/\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno idea\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nany\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nany\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\npacman",
